On December 20, 2017, President Trump gave remarks on the passing of the Tax Cuts and Jobs Act. He called it the largest tax cut in the history of the United States and praised the benefits it would provide to American families and businesses. He also highlighted the inclusion of the Arctic National Wildlife Refuge (ANWR) in the bill, which he said was a historic achievement. Several members of Congress and Cabinet members spoke as well, expressing their gratitude to the President and their belief that the tax reform would lead to economic growth and job creation. The President concluded by thanking the individuals who had worked on the bill for years.